The paper focuses on spectrum sensing, which is a key topic in wireless communication and falls under the sub-categories of information theory (cs.IT), networking and internet architecture (cs.NI), signal processing (cs.SI), cryptography and security (cs.CR), and machine learning (cs.LG). However, since the paper deals with the detection of signals in the presence of noise, it is most likely to belong to the sub-categories of information theory (cs.IT) and networking and internet architecture (cs.NI).
